[1844, 03-02] Ms.A.9.2.20.16-17

Sturge, Esther, to MWC; London. The writer regrets that JQA disclaims
being an Abolitionist. ... Asks if JAC deserted the cause. Says she does
not wholly agree with Joseph Sturge. “I am sorry to see in a letter of
T. Clarkson’s he attributes the idea of setting slaves in West Indies
free to William Allen ere the term of Apprenticeship expired.” Says that
Zachary Macaulay was the real emancipator. W. Allen opposed immediate
emancipation.


